Instructions for building Tanuki's Java Service Wrapper (JSW) on Windows 2008 64 bits
=============

1. Donwload JSW sources
URL: http://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/download/3.3.1/wrapper_3.3.1_src.zip
There is a more recent version but 3.3.1 is the version RHQ is currently using.

2. Patch the sources
Unzip wrapper_3.3.1_src.zip
Copy wrapper_3.3.1_src.patch next to wrapper_3.3.1_src directory
Apply the patch file: patch -p0 < wrapper_3.3.1_src.patch

3. Prepare the Windows 2008 box
Copy the patched directory somewhere in your Windows 2008 box
Install a 64 bits JDK (www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html)
Install ANT (works with 1.9.2) (http://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi)
Install Visual C++ Express 2010 (http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/fra/downloads#d-2010-express)
Install Windows 2008 SDK (http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=11310)

4. Build
Open a command prompt and move to wrapper_3.3.1_src directory
Run build64.bat

5. Artifacts
The following artifacts should be built:
* wrapper_3.3.1_src\bin\wrapper.exe
* wrapper_3.3.1_src\lib\wrapper.dll
* wrapper_3.3.1_src\lib\wrapper.jar

